Alas. I am not a nurse. And I’ve never pursued any further education. Even though I know I’d be an excellent ob/gyn nurse midwife.
The nursing proctor said that it wasn’t that distracting and if I couldn’t handle that I couldn’t be a nurse.
ADHD is a such a damn trip. The only test I failed was one where the girl crying behind me distracted me so much it gave me a panic attack. I had an adhd/ptsd diagnosis already. Didn’t matter.
And I couldn’t continue because I had no support system except for “try harder” and “I thought you could do this with less classes” (9 credits instead of a full 15)
I didn’t fail tests because I didn’t have the knowledge. I failed because I couldn’t concentrate.

Coming to terms with one’s ADHD is a trip. 

It just dawned on me, I didn’t drop out of nursing school because I was failing. I had a B+ average. I dropped out because I was being emotionally and financially abused into going to nursing school because teaching didn’t pay.
